<item>
            <title>[SEC-692] Introduce NoneChannelProcessor</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-692</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was wondering if it might be a good idea to add a NoneChannelProcessor to acegi that does nothing but serves as a way to specify excludes &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Take the following scenario&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;channelProcessingFilter&quot; class=&quot;org.acegisecurity.securechannel.ChannelProcessingFilter&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;property name=&quot;filterInvocationDefinitionSource&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      CONVERT_URL_TO_LOWERCASE_BEFORE_COMPARISON&lt;br/&gt;
      PATTERN_TYPE_APACHE_ANT&lt;br/&gt;
      /secure/**=REQUIRES_SECURE_CHANNEL&lt;br/&gt;
      /**=REQUIRES_INSECURE_CHANNEL&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suppose you have a number of images that can be used  in both secure and non secure pages, you do not want the ChannelProcessingFilter to do a redirect for these images. &lt;br/&gt;
In the above configuration that will happen because of the catch-all at the end&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To solve this one could not use the catch-all and instead explicitly list all urls for which a redirect to an insecure channel should be used but that would be both brittle and a lot of work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;allowing you to specify something similar to &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/image/**=#NONE#  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;would make make for easier configuration and would be consistent with the way FilterChainProxy works&lt;/p&gt;</description>
